      "span_text": "A focus group is a group interview, centred on a specific topic and facilitated and coordinated by a moderator, that seeks to generate qualitative data by capitalising on the interaction that occurs within the group setting. [CITATION_1] The aim of the focus groups was to elicit the perceptions, feelings, attitudes and everyday experiences of physiotherapists in relation to confidentiality.",
